<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2021, &ldquo;On the Topic of Emergence from
an Effective Field Theory Perspective&rdquo;, in <em>Top-Down
Causation and Emergence</em>, Jan Voosholz and Markus Gabriel (eds.),
(Synthese Library), Cham: Springer International Publishing,
101&ndash;114. </li>

<li>Mainwood, Paul, 2006, <em>Is More Different? Emergent Properties
in Physics</em>, PhD, University of Oxford.
 [<a href="https://philsci-archive.pitt.edu/8339/" target="other">Mainwood 2006 available online</a>]</li>
 
<li>Manohar, Aneesh V., 1997, &ldquo;Effective Field Theories&rdquo;,
in <em>Perturbative and Nonperturbative Aspects of Quantum Field
Theory: Proceedings of the 35. Internationale Universit&auml;tswochen
f&uuml;r Kern- und Teilchenphysik, Schladming, Austria, March
2&ndash;9, 1996</em>, H. Latal and W. Schweiger (eds.), (Lecture Notes
in Physics 479), Berlin/New York: Springer, 311&ndash;362.
doi:10.1007/BFb0104294</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2020, &ldquo;Introduction to Effective
Field Theories&rdquo;, in <em>Effective Field Theory in Particle
Physics and Cosmology</em>, Sacha Davidson, Paolo Gambino, Mikko
Laine, Matthias Neubert, and Christophe Salomon (eds), Oxford: Oxford
University Press, 47&ndash;136.
doi:10.1093/oso/9780198855743.003.0002</li>

<li>Matsubara, Keizo, 2013, &ldquo;Realism, Underdetermination and
String Theory Dualities&rdquo;, <em>Synthese</em>, 190(3):
471&ndash;489. doi:10.1007/s11229-011-0041-3</li>

<li>McGivern, Patrick, 2008, &ldquo;Reductive Levels and Multi-Scale
Structure&rdquo;, <em>Synthese</em>, 165(1): 53&ndash;75.
doi:10.1007/s11229-007-9232-3</li>

<li>McKenzie, Kerry, 2019, &ldquo;Fundamentality&rdquo;, in <em>The
Routledge Handbook of Emergence</em>, Sophie Gibb, Robin Findlay, and
Tom Lancaster (eds.), Abingdon/New York: Routledge, 54&ndash;64 (ch.
3).</li>



<li>Morganti, Matteo, 2020a, &ldquo;Fundamentality in Metaphysics and
the Philosophy of Physics. Part I: Metaphysics&rdquo;, <em>Philosophy
Compass</em>, 15(7): e12690. doi:10.1111/phc3.12690</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2020b, &ldquo;Fundamentality in Metaphysics
and the Philosophy of Physics. Part II: The Philosophy of
Physics&rdquo;, <em>Philosophy Compass</em>, 15(10): e12703.
doi:10.1111/phc3.12703</li>

<li>Morrison, Margaret, 2012, &ldquo;Emergent Physics and
Micro-Ontology&rdquo;, <em>Philosophy of Science</em>, 79(1):
141&ndash;166. doi:10.1086/663240</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2015, &ldquo;Why Is More Different?&rdquo;,
in <em>Why More Is Different: Philosophical Issues in Condensed Matter
Physics and Complex Systems</em>, Brigitte Falkenburg and Margaret
Morrison (eds.), (The Frontiers Collection), Berlin/Heidelberg:
Springer, 91&ndash;114. doi:10.1007/978-3-662-43911-1_6</li>

<li>Moulines, C. Ulises, 1980, &ldquo;Intertheoretic Approximation:
The Kepler-Newton Case&rdquo;, <em>Synthese</em>, 45(3):
387&ndash;412. doi:10.1007/BF02221785</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1984, &ldquo;Ontological Reduction in the
Natural Sciences (1)&rdquo;, in <em>Reduction in Science: Structure,
Examples, Philosophical Problems</em>, Wolfgang Balzer, David A.
Pearce, and Heinz-J&uuml;rgen Schmidt (eds.), Dordrecht: Springer
